<TITLE> Nine die in Sirajganj, Chittagong road accidents </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Sirajganj/Chittagong, Dec 20 (bdnews24.com)Nine people were killed and at least 50 injured in two separate road accidents in Chittagong and Sirajganj Thursday. Eight people died, and at least 40 were seriously hurt, in a single accident after a cattle truck collided with a van and a motorcycle at around 11am on the main Dhaka-Sirajganj highway near Konabari in Kamarkhanda, police said. As the truck was fleeing the scene it overturned into a ditch. Konabari police sub-inspector Md Shahjahan Hossain told bdnews24.com that the eight people who were killed included the motorcycle driver, the driver and one passenger of the van and 5 cattle workers on the truck that overturned. The dead have not been identified as yet, said Hossain. In Mirershorai, Chittagong, a bus driver died and five were wounded as a bus and truck met in a head-on collision, police said. At 6am, a bus travelling to Chittagong collided with a truck going in the opposite direction, Mirershorai police said. Bus driver Selim died on the spot. The injured were taken to local hospitals. Both vehicles have been impounded by police. bdnews24.co
